The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the United States Capitol Rotunda to commemorate the life and service of Senator John McCain. He mentioned McCain's military background, his time as a prisoner of war, and his service in Congress. Pence spoke about McCain's support for limited government, tax reform, and the armed forces. He also shared a personal anecdote about traveling with McCain to visit troops overseas. Pence highlighted McCain's love for the men and women in the military and his commitment to putting country first. He concluded by expressing condolences to McCain's family and praying for their comfort.